Runbook: DLP Investigation (Evidence → Conclusion)
Goal
Build a complete picture of what happened and decide: benign, policy gap, or incident. 
Steps
1.	Review Alert Details
o	What rule/policy matched and why 
o	What sensitive content was detected 
o	What action occurred (share/copy/upload/paste/print/etc.) 
2.	Gather Related Activity
o	Look for patterns: repeated attempts, multi-step behavior, cross-location attempts  
3.	Determine Root Cause Category
o	Accidental user behavior (education opportunity) 
o	Policy gap / mis-scope (tuning needed) 
o	Suspicious / malicious indicators (potential escalation) 
4.	Decide Outcome
o	Informational: document and close 
o	True Positive – Low/Medium: user follow-up + scoped remediation + policy tuning 
o	True Positive – High Risk: invoke incident response path consistent with your organization (detection/analysis → containment → eradication → recovery → post-incident). 
Output Artifacts
•	Investigation notes, ownership, status update (resolved/closed), and tuning recommendation. 
